===2020 census===
As of the [[2020 United States census|2020 census]], there were 82 people, 41 households, and 26 families residing in the city.<ref name="Census2020DP">{{cite web|title=2020 Decennial Census Demographic Profile (DP1)|url=https://api.census.gov/data/2020/dec/dp?get=NAME,DP1_0021P,DP1_0024P,DP1_0025C,DP1_0049C,DP1_0045C,DP1_0069C,DP1_0073C,DP1_0125P,DP1_0126P,DP1_0129P,DP1_0133P,DP1_0137P,DP1_0138P,DP1_0139P,DP1_0141P,DP1_0142P,DP1_0143P,DP1_0145P,DP1_0146P,DP1_0147C,DP1_0148C,DP1_0149C,DP1_0156C,DP1_0157C,DP1_0158C,DP1_0159P,DP1_0160P&for=place%3A34365&in=state%3A19|website=United States Census Bureau|year=2021|access-date=May 1, 2026|df=mdy}}</ref><ref name="Census2020PL">{{cite web|title=2020 Decennial Census Redistricting Data (Public Law 94-171)|url=https://api.census.gov/data/2020/dec/pl?get=NAME,P1_001N,P1_003N,P1_004N,P1_005N,P1_006N,P1_007N,P1_008N,P1_009N,P2_001N,P2_002N,H1_001N,H1_002N&for=place%3A34365&in=state%3A19|website=United States Census Bureau|year=2021|access-date=May 1, 2026|df=mdy}}</ref> The [[population density]] was 365.8 inhabitants per square mile (141.2/km<sup>2</sup>). There were 44 housing units at an average density of 196.3 per square mile (75.8/km<sup>2</sup>).<ref name="Census2020DP"/>

The median age in the city was 46.5 years. 19.5% of residents were under the age of 18. 20.7% of residents were under the age of 20; 4.9% were between the ages of 20 and 24; 24.4% were from 25 to 44; 20.7% were from 45 to 64; and 29.3% were 65 years of age or older. For every 100 females, there were 110.3 males, and for every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 106.2 males age 18 and over.<ref name="Census2020DP"/><ref name="Census2020PL"/>

Of these households, 46.3% had children under the age of 18 living with them; 48.8% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together; 9.8% were cohabitating couples; 24.4% had a female householder with no spouse or partner present; and 17.1% had a male householder with no spouse or partner present. 36.6% of all households were non-families. 31.7% of all households were made up of individuals, and 9.8% had someone living alone who was 65 years old or older.<ref name="Census2020DP"/>

Of all housing units, 6.8% were vacant. The homeowner vacancy rate was 0.0% and the rental vacancy rate was 0.0%. All residents lived in rural areas.<ref name="Census2020DP"/><ref name="Census2020DHC">{{cite web|title=2020 Decennial Census Demographic and Housing Characteristics (DHC)|url=https://api.census.gov/data/2020/dec/dhc?get=NAME,P2_002N,P2_003N&for=place%3A34365&in=state%3A19|website=United States Census Bureau|year=2023|access-date=May 1, 2026|df=mdy}}</ref>

